    {
      "id": "1a9dcd25_24f53383",
      "file_path": "POLICY-SDK-APP/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/admin/PolicyRestController.java",
      "patchset_number": 4,
      "line": 355,
      "message": "Sonar will complain about nested try/catch here. Also I think the cyclic complexity of this method is likely to be high. One suggestion would be to replace the highlighted code with a private method called doConnect(), something like:\n\nreturn doConnect(connection);\n\nprivate String doConnect(final HttpURLConnection connection() throws <someExceptions> {\n    connection.connect();\n    int responseCode = connection.getResponseCode();\n    if(responseCode == 200){\n\t// get the response content into a String\n\tString responseJson = null;\n\t// read the inputStream into a buffer (trick found online scans entire input looking for end-of-file)\n\ttry (java.util.Scanner scanner = new java.util.Scanner(connection.getInputStream())) {\n\t    scanner.useDelimiter(\"\\\\A\");\n\t    responseJson = scanner.hasNext() ? scanner.next() : \"\";\n\t} catch (Exception e){\n\t    //Reason for rethrowing the exception is if any exception occurs during reading of inputsteam\n\t    //then the exception handling is done by the outer block without returning the response immediately\n\t    //Also finally block is existing only in outer block and not here so all exception handling is\n\t    //done in only one place\n\t    policyLogger.error(\"Exception Occured\"+e);\n\t    throw e;\n\t}\n\n\tpolicyLogger.info(\"JSON response from PAP: \" + responseJson);\n\treturn responseJson;\n    }\n}\n\nReplace <someExceptions> in the method declaration with whatever exceptions the method throws.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 2787,
        "name": "Liam Fallon",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "liam.fallon@est.tech",
        "username": "liamfallon"
      },
      "updated": "2018-07-17 08:03:12.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "1a9dcd25_842be7ea",
      "file_path": "POLICY-SDK-APP/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/admin/RESTfulPAPEngine.java",
      "patchset_number": 4,
      "line": 465,
      "message": "You could try the same technique here (create a private method) to solve the nested try issue.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 2787,
        "name": "Liam Fallon",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "liam.fallon@est.tech",
        "username": "liamfallon"
      },
      "updated": "2018-07-17 08:03:12.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": false
